(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Tenses.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind past, present, future, and) Tj
T*
(consistent verb forms.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct interpretation or writing method step by step instead of jumping to) Tj
T*
(the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on changing a paragraph from present tense to past tense.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in past, present, future, and consistent verb forms that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Tenses step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
